text: Then why are most of Trump's complaints about not being "thanked" for the funeral? Also, here's a hint: John McCain is dead. So he will not be "thanking" Trump anytime soon. All of that seems rather petty, as I said.
author: ScottJW

text: And finally, as a Christian, I think our heart and compassion should be directed towards the McCain family and remembering their grief. Differences should be let go. In the end, John McCain was a patriot who loved his country. Let's remember him that way. (4)
author: ScottJW

text: I didn't always agree with McCain, but he was a patriot who loved his country. And regardless of Trump's gripes with the Senator (or our wish that he voted to repeal ObamaCare), McCain is gone now. Continuing a one-sided feud is petty. (3)
author: ScottJW

text: People shouldn't defend Trump's continuing attack on McCain. They shouldn't explain it away. It's simply wrong.  Continuing to attack a man whose family is still deeply grieving is beneath the office of the presidency. (2)
author: ScottJW

text: This shouldn't have to be said, but the President of the United States should not be insulting and harassing the memory and the family of a dead war hero. What Donald Trump is doing to the McCain family is wrong. Period. (1)
author: ScottJW
